This tests PRD 7 US-001 (reset hasEverHadPlugins). Follow the pattern from e2e/onboarding.e2e.ts which already tests the onboarding flow.

The test flow:
1. Start server WITH plugins -> side panel shows plugins -> hasEverHadPlugins is set to true
2. Restart server WITHOUT plugins -> side panel shows ReturningUserEmptyState
3. Find and click the 'Show setup guide' link
4. Verify OnboardingState appears (Welcome to OpenTabs, checklist)

This is a complex test requiring server restart with different configs. Follow the onboarding.e2e.ts pattern which uses manual infrastructure setup.

```typescript
test('show setup guide resets onboarding', async () => {
  // Phase 1: Start with plugins to set hasEverHadPlugins
  const configDir = createTestConfigDir(); // has e2e-test plugin
  const server = await startMcpServer(configDir, true);
  const { context, cleanupDir, extensionDir } = await launchExtensionContext(server.port);
  setupAdapterSymlink(configDir, extensionDir);
  await waitForExtensionConnected(server);

  const sidePanelPage = await openSidePanel(context);
  // Wait for plugins to show (sets hasEverHadPlugins)
  await expect(sidePanelPage.getByText('E2E Test')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 30_000 });

  // Phase 2: Remove all plugins
  await server.kill();
  const config = await readTestConfig(configDir);
  config.localPlugins = [];
  await writeTestConfig(configDir, config);
  const server2 = await startMcpServer(configDir, true, server.port);
  // ... reconnect, verify returning user state

  // Phase 3: Click 'Show setup guide'
  await sidePanelPage.reload();
  await expect(sidePanelPage.getByText('No Plugins Installed')).toBeVisible({ timeout: 30_000 });
  await sidePanelPage.getByText('Show setup guide').click();
  await expect(sidePanelPage.getByText('Welcome to OpenTabs')).toBeVisible();

  // Cleanup
  ...
});
```

