This tests PRD 5 US-001 (source maps). This is more of a build artifact test than a runtime E2E test. It can be a unit test in platform/plugin-tools or a lightweight E2E test.

For the E2E approach, check the e2e-test plugin's build output:

```typescript
import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';
import path from 'node:path';

test('plugin build generates source map', async () => {
  const pluginDir = path.resolve('plugins/e2e-test');
  const iifeContent = readFileSync(path.join(pluginDir, 'dist/adapter.iife.js'), 'utf-8');

  // Check sourceMappingURL comment exists
  expect(iifeContent).toContain('//# sourceMappingURL=');

  // Check .map file exists
  const mapPath = path.join(pluginDir, 'dist/adapter.iife.js.map');
  expect(existsSync(mapPath)).toBe(true);

  // Validate source map structure
  const sourceMap = JSON.parse(readFileSync(mapPath, 'utf-8'));
  expect(sourceMap.version).toBe(3);
  expect(sourceMap.sources).toBeDefined();
  expect(sourceMap.mappings).toBeDefined();
});
```

This can go in a new e2e/build-artifacts.e2e.ts or as a unit test in platform/plugin-tools/src/commands/build.test.ts.
